<|startoftext|>Really like Freshii, it's one of the better Italian restaurants in the west valley. It's tucked right by my work so I decided to give it a shot. \n\nOur server was great at introducing us to a wide variety of menu items. I got the Chicken Gorgonzola pizza (we shared) for the two of us. It was an excellent size, very similar to a larger size chicken pizza I've had elsewhere. I love sauce like this so it was a nice surprise to find it a good part of my menu.\n\nThe portion size was impressive for a $10 pizza. It was generous and didn't get boring. The garlic cheese and pesto was to die for. Also I really like that in this menu it's separate dishes for each item. Everything tasted together in a good way.\n\nThe prices are a bit high but this place is well worth it. I wish there was more options like this in the valley because I do see a lot of mediocre places with expensive sandwiches and really poor service.<|endoftext|>
