<|startoftext|>I've given many, many, and good deeds to the Southeastern Conference (SEC)...now it's time to give Mike Riley his share. Not only is he a great coach, the entire staff treats him like a King of Spades (AKA, a better deal of his) and I believe in him more than most anybody alive. \n\nFirst, he is absolutely an honest guy. When I was making suggestions to him for a nickname or for anything about to take the next day I knew exactly what Mike and the whole staff would be asking and more importantly, knowing that he won't do anything with it. He doesn't have any ulterior motives when it comes to things like who he wants to be at Florida or anywhere.\n\nSecond, he really cares. He gets what he wants and more than enough about what he likes (which I think is pretty rare among coaches). My first night at FI is the last time I can remember my first time being around a SEC facility. I've never left feeling like I could do it again, especially when I know the entire staff could care less, and that's exactly how Mike Riley sets up his facility.\n\nThird, we love him or hate him it's a never ending story. \n\nMike's an extremely hard worker who has worked for many years in the game. The entire staff at FI just loves him and respect him. Mike and the entire staff is not only great individuals but they really care about what they're doing.\n\nMike Riley is a winner.<|endoftext|>
